#week-title("Three", "The Three Principles in the Self: Final Mapping")

=== Core Teaching

The constitutional mapping of the three principles in the self — first
conducted in Year Two Month 8 — is now revisited for the final time within
the curriculum. The purpose is not to compare against the Year Two mapping
in order to measure progress, but to receive an accurate picture of the
practitioner's current constitution as they approach the end of the formal
curriculum.

Three years of alchemical practice — of calcination (burning away the
unnecessary), of distillation (lifting and clarifying what is essential), and
of cohobation (reuniting what was separated at a higher level) — have changed
the practitioner's constitution. Not always in the direction they expected, and
not always visibly. But the inner alchemical process has been operating
continuously alongside the laboratory work.

*The final mapping:*

*Sulphur — the soul, the animating flame:* What is the quality of your deepest
passion and characteristic force now, compared to Year One? Has the Sulphur
been purified — more specific, more essential, less mixed with ego and
performative enthusiasm? Or has it been diminished — the fire lower, the
passion more cautious? Both are possible outcomes of the Work; only honesty
reveals which has occurred.

*Mercury — the spirit, the connecting intelligence:* What is the quality of
your connective intelligence after three years? Is it more fluid, more capable
of holding complexity without forcing resolution? Is it faster or slower? More
perceptive of subtle connections, or more disciplined in not following every
association?

*Salt — the body, the fixed structure:* What is the quality of your persistent
structure — your habits, your physical patterns, your characteristic way of
engaging with the Work — after three years? What has been fixed that was
previously volatile? What has been dissolved that was previously rigid?

The final mapping does not require that the three principles be in perfect
balance. The tradition is clear that perfect balance is the Stone — not the
practitioner. But an honest mapping reveals where the Work is most needed and
most alive.

=== Topics This Week

- The final constitutional mapping: Sulphur, Mercury, Salt in the present self
- Comparing to the Year Two Month 8 mapping without judgment
- What three years of practice changes and what it does not
- Writing the final constitutional map in the inner work journal

